HEADWORD: Prosobranchiata
<hw>Pros`o*bran`chi*a"ta</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos>
<ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <?/ forward, further + <?/ a gill.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The highest division, or subclass, of gastropod
mollusks, including those that have the gills situated anteriorly, or
forward of the heart, and the sexes separate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

